'byung pos zin|This is likely an alternate Tibetan translation for the Sanskrit phrase *bhūtagraha, more commonly rendered in Tibetan as {'byung po'i gdon}. The phrase shares semantic resonances with the compound bhūta grahāviṣṭa/{'byung po'i gdon gyis non pa} and the Sanskrit bhūtāveśa, all of which refer to being possessed by a class of spirit (bhūta/{'byung po}).
