'byung po|The name of a certain brahmin who lived in Rājagṛha.\nNot to be confused with Bhūta, the name of a merchant and a dog, and a certain class of evil beings.
'byung po|A ghost in the Indian tradition, sometimes haunting houses where they were killed. They can appear in human or animal form. They cast no shadow and their feet are always backward. In Hindi they are called bhoot.
'byung po|The name of a certain householder’s dog and the name given to the lost infant it carried home to its owner one night, which would one day be reunited with his birth mother.\nAlso the name of a certain brahmin who lived in Rājagṛha, and the name of a certain class of evil beings.
