'khor bzhi po|These are monks, nuns, and male and female followers of the householder code of conduct.
'khor bzhi po|The assemblies of monks (Skt. bhikṣu) and nuns (Skt. bhikṣuṇī), along with laymen (Skt. upāsaka) and laywomen (Skt. upāsikā).
'khor bzhi|Monks, nuns, and male and female lay practitioners.
'khor bzhi|Male and female monastics and males and females holding lay vows.
'khor bzhi|Male and female lay followers, and male and female monastic followers.
'khor bzhi|The “fourfold assembly” consists of monks, nuns, and male and female lay practitioners.
'khor bzhi|This denotes the assemblies of fully ordained monks and nuns, along with laymen and laywomen.
