a ti sha|Atiśa Dīpaṃkara śrī jñāna (982–1054 ce), often referred to in Tibetan as {jo bo}, “(The) Lord,” was a renowned figure in the history of Tibetan Buddhism famous for coming to Tibet and revitalizing Buddhism there during the early eleventh century.
