bla na med pa yang dag par rdzogs pa'i byang chub|The awakening of a buddha, which is superior to all other forms of awakening. According to the Mahāyāna, in anuttara samyak saṃbodhi, both of the two kinds of obscuration, the afflictive obscuration (Skt. kleśāvaraṇa) and the obscurations to omniscience (Skt. jñeyāvaraṇa), have been completely overcome.
