cho ga zhib mo'i rgyal po|Literally “king of rites,” the term can refer to an actual ritual or a ritual text, such as the AP.
cho ga|A ritual or a rite; in our presentation it is translated as “ritual” when it refers to a group or a cycle of rites, and as “rite” when it refers to an individual rite (the distinction, however, is blurred). The term can also refer to a text that is a collection of rites, such as the AP, in the sense of a manual of rites.
