chos kyi lta|Birthplace of the buddha Madhura svara rāja.
chos kyi lus|Distinct from the rūpakāya or “form body” of a buddha. In origin it was a term for the presence of the Dharma, which would continue after the Buddha’s passing. It also came to refer to someone who was an embodiment of the Dharma, and also the eternal, imperceptible realization of a buddha, and therefore became synonymous with the true nature. In the context of the teaching of the three kāyas of a buddha, only the term dharmakāya ({chos kyi sku}), rather than dharmaśarīra, ({chos kyi lus}) was used.
