chos kyi rnam grangs|An explication of the Dharma.
chos kyi rnam grangs|This may refer to the entire text of the Ratnaketudhāraṇī or to a section dealing with a particular dhāraṇī.
chos kyi rnam grangs|In Buddhism, lit. “method” or “means of teaching the doctrine,” denoting both the ways of teaching the dharma as well as the dharma discourse itself.
chos kyi rnam grangs|The word paryāya regularly has the sense of “method,” “procedure,” “approach,” but here it is simply “Dharma teaching,” “Dharma discourse,” or more literally, “approach to the Dharma.” The Chinese fa men (lit. “door to the Dharma”) conveys the sense of “access/approach” and by extension, “teaching.” The Tibetan {rnam grangs} easily misleads people into thinking that this has something to do with “enumeration.”
