gling bzhi|According to Abhidharma cosmology, each world system has four continents surrounding a central Mount Meru: to the east, Videha ({lus 'phags po}, “superior body”); to the south, our continent of Jambudvīpa ({'dzam bu gling}, “Rose Apple Continent”); to the west, Apara godānīya ({ba glang spyod} “Rich in Cattle”); and to the north, Uttarakuru ({sgra mi snyan}, “Unpleasant Sound”).
