gsang tshig|One of ten different kinds of verbal phrase or statement (Skt. pada) mentioned in this text.
gsang tshig|Literally “an instrument of thought,” it is usually a brief verbal formula used in multiple repetitions, usually beginning with oṁ and in essence a salutation to a particular deity.
