man dA ra ba|Erythrina indica or Erythrina variegata. Also known as mandarava, flame tree, and tiger’s claw. In the summer it is covered in large crimson flowers, which are believed to also grow in Indra’s paradise. The coral tree is the most widespread species of Erythrina or mandārava, taller than the others, and all are collectively known as coral trees.
