mchod yon|The offering consisting mainly of water for washing the feet, washing the hands, or rinsing the mouth, which is offered to a guest (or a summoned deity) to welcome them or bid them farewell.
mchod yon|Typically an offering of water for the feet, but can include other items offered to welcome a guest. In the Bhūta ḍāmara Tantra, however, it often consists of an article of food and is, on some occasions, referred to as bali.
