mos pa spyod pa'i sa|An early stage in a bodhisattva’s career during which they have developed a degree of conviction that is not yet informed by direct experience. The level of devoted engagement is said to comprise the first two of the five paths, those of accumulation and preparation, which lead up to the path of seeing. This level is also presented as the second of seven spiritual levels in the Bodhisattvabhūmi,https://read.84000.co/translation/toh4037.html which follows the initial level of the spiritual potential (gotrabhūmi).
