nang du yang dag 'jog la gnas pa|One of a number of lifestyles that Buddhist monks might adopt, it is particularly conducive to practicing meditation and is thus associated with monks who valued meditation as an integral part of their lives as ascetics. The Tibetan {nang du yang dag 'jog pa} can correspond to the Sanskrit pratisaṃlāyana or pratisaṁlīna.
