rdul|One of the three principles or forces of nature, as known in the Sāṃkhya philosophy, characterized by energy and movement.
rdul|A son of King Diśāṃpati of Pāṁśula who lived before the time of Buddha Śākyamuni. He became king after the death of his father. In The Hundred Deeds, he is said to have been a previous incarnation of King Bimbisāra.
