ri dags 'dzin gyi ma|Another name for Viśākhā Mṛgāramātā, a lay follower of the Buddha.
ri dags 'dzin gyi ma|This is the nickname of an upāsikā (female lay practitioner), actually called Viśākhā, who is sometimes considered the most prominent among female lay followers of the Buddha. She had married the son of a man called Mṛgāra, who was originally a Jaina but went to meet the Buddha and even become a stream enterer thanks to her. Feeling indebted to her, he said that she was like his mother, which is the origin of the nickname.
