rnal 'byor|Literally “union” in Sanskrit; Tibetan specifies “union with the natural state.”
rnal 'byor|A term which is generally used to refer to a wide range of spiritual practices. It literally means to be merged with or “yoked to,” in the sense of being fully immersed in one’s respective discipline. The Tibetan specifies “union with the natural state.”
