rnam par bzhi'i gzigs|Probably a variant of the Buddha’s five observations (pañcadarśana), the five predeterminations of Buddha Śākyamuni before he came to this world: (1) {dus la gzigs pa}, observation of the time for his appearance; (2) {rus la gzigs pa}, observation of the family of his birth; (3) {rigs la gzigs pa}, observation of the caste of his lineage; (4) {yum la gzigs pa}, observation of the mother to whom he would be born; and (5) {yul la gzigs pa}, observation of the land in which to disseminate his doctrine (Rigzin 366).
