sgrib pa lnga|These are five mental impediments that hinder meditation: impediments of desire (kāmacchanda), malice (vyāpāda), depression and sloth (styānamiddha), wildness and excitement (auddhatya kaukṛtya), and doubt, or perplexity (vicikitsa).
sgrib pa lnga|The five obscurations, as found in https://read.84000.co/translation/UT22084-031-002.html#UT22084-031-002-2531 , comprise longing for sensual pleasure, agitation and regret, harmful intention, dullness and sleepiness, and hesitation. See also Kimura IV: 182.
