skyil krung phye pa|There are two versions of ardhaparyaṅka posture—one sitting, the other dancing. In the CMT, this term refers to the former.
skyil krung phyed pa|There are two versions of the ardhaparyaṅka posture—one sitting, the other dancing.
skyil mo krung gi steng du skye ba|A realm of the triple-lute-bearer gods.
skyil mo krung|There are two versions of ardhaparyaṅka posture: the first is sitting with one foot drawn in and the other extended, and the second is dancing. Wrathful deities, such as Krodharāja, tend to assume the latter. In this posture the deity is standing on the tips of their toes with their left leg slightly bent, while the right leg, with the knee pointing to the right, kicks upward to the height of the left knee.
