stong chen po|“The great thousand, three thousand-fold universe,” a cosmological term that signifies the entire universe.
stong chen|The largest universe described in Buddhist cosmology. This term, in Abhidharma cosmology, refers to 1,000³ world systems, i.e., 1,000 “dichiliocosms” or “two thousand great thousand world realms” (dvi sāhasra mahā sāhasra lokadhātu), which are in turn made up of 1,000 first-order world systems, each with its own Mount Meru, continents, sun, and moon, etc.
