tsha ba|The hell called “hot.” Traditionally the sixth of the eight hot hells.
tsha ba|Apart from referring to fever itself, the term is also used as the name of the spirits that cause it.
tsha ba|Sixth of the eight hot hells of Buddhist cosmology. Inhabitants of this hell are boiled in cauldrons, roasted in pans, beaten with hammers, and skewered with spears as their bodies burst into flame.
