yongs su mya ngan las 'da' ba|The final stage of passing into nirvāṇa, which occurs when an arhat or a buddha passes away.
yongs su mya ngan las 'da' pa|“Complete nirvāṇa”; the term used when referring to the passing away of a fully realized being.
yongs su mya ngan las 'das pa chen po|Synonym of “parinirvāṇa.”
