yul 'khor srung|One of the Four Great Kings ({rgyal po chen po bzhi}) ruling the four directions of the desire realm. Dhṛtarāṣṭra rules the eastern direction and the gandharvas ({dri za}) that reside there. In The Question of Mañjuśrī the image of him is the forty-ninth of the eighty designs on the palms and soles of the Tathāgata.
