zhe sdang|Hatred, aggression, and/or aversion. One of the affective behavior patterns or “afflictions” known as the three poisons.
zhe sdang|Second of the five fetters associated with the lower realms; one of the three poisons ({dug gsum}) which, along with desire and delusion, perpetuate the sufferings of cyclic existence. In its subtle manifestation as aversion it obstructs the correct perception of forms, and in its extreme manifestation as hatred and fear, it is characteristic of the hells.
